    <stitle>CF 500, CF 600 Steering - Steering Column Switches - Removal and Installation</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>Removal and Installation</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Steering Column Multifunction Switch</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the battery ground cable. For additional information, refer to
                    <exhotlnk document="../S08/S08307.htm" bookname="S08307">Battery, Mounting and Cables in
                        S08307</exhotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the steering wheel. For additional information, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s05017_X2110422.xml" xrefid="x2110422">Steering Column</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 3 steering column cover screws, then remove the 2 steering column covers.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1105005" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025284.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the turn signal/headlamp switch and the windshield wiper switch electrical
                    connectors.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 4 screws, then remove the multifunction switch assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1105006" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025287.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 2 screws, then remove the windshield wiper switch.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1105007" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025288.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 2 screws, then remove the turn signal/headlamp switch.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1105008" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025289.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install, reverse the removal procedure.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Ignition Switch Removal</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the battery ground cable. For additional information, refer to
                    <exhotlnk document="../S08/S08307.htm" bookname="S08307">Battery, Mounting and Cables in
                        S08307</exhotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 3 steering column cover screws, then remove the 2 steering column covers.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1105009" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025284.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the ignition switch and the key-in-ignition switch electrical connectors.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a hammer and a chisel, make a groove in the heads of the ignition switch assembly
                    mounting bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1105010" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../fign00/N0025292.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 2 bolts and the ignition switch assembly.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Ignition Switch Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the ignition switch assembly onto the steering column by aligning the key
                    cylinder with the groove in the steering shaft. Verify ignition switch operation by inserting the
                    key into the ignition switch. Do not turn the ignition key.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The mounting bracket bolts are designed so that when the correct torque specification is
                        achieved, the bolt heads will break off. Use hand tools when tightening the bolts, the use of a
                        torque wrench is not necessary.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the mounting bracket and install 2 new mounting bolts.</para>
                <para>&#8226; Tighten the bolts until the bolt heads break off.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the ignition switch and the key-in-ignition switch electrical connectors.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the 2 steering column covers, then install the 3 steering column cover
                    screws.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the battery ground cable. For additional information, refer to
                    <exhotlnk document="../S08/S08307.htm" bookname="S08307">Battery, Mounting and Cables in
                        S08307</exhotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
